Get a list of Stics xml parameters names and values from a table (data.frame, tibble)

Source: R/get_params_from_table.R
get_params_from_table.Rd

Get a list of Stics xml parameters names and values from a table (data.frame, tibble)

get_params_from_table(
  params_table,
  param_names = NULL,
  xml_doc,
  lines_id = NULL,
  stopping = FALSE,
  dict = NULL
)

Arguments

params_table

a table (df, tibble) containing parameters to use
param_names

parameters names to select
xml_doc

an xmlDocument object (of any xml type)
lines_id

table lines identifiers to select
stopping

logical value for stopping if any unknown parameters (if TRUE)
dict

List of names correspondence between short names (tags) and real parameters names

Value

a named list (with param names as list names) of data.frame/tibble

Examples

if (FALSE) {

download_usm_xl(xl_name = "inputs_stics_example.xlsx", dest_dir = "/path/to/dest/dir")
xl_path <- file.path("/path/to/dest/dir","inputs_stics_example.xlsx")
ini_param_df <- read_excel(xl_path, sheet = "Ini")
xml_path <- "path/to/ini/xml"
ini_doc <- SticsRFiles:::xmldocument(xml_path)
get_params_from_table(ini_param_df, ini_doc)

}
